import pandas as pd
import requests
import io

URL = "https://cf-courses-data.s3.us.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud/IBMDeveloperSkillsNetwork-DV0101EN-SkillsNetwork/Data%20Files/Historical_Wildfires.csv"

# Fetch the data using requests
response = requests.get(URL)

# Create a BytesIO object from the content
text = io.BytesIO(response.content)

# Read the CSV into a pandas dataframe
df = pd.read_csv(text)

# Print a message
print('Data read into a pandas dataframe!')

This plot represents that the estimated fire area was on its peak after 2011, April and before 2012. You can verify on google/news, this was the time of maximum wildfire hit in Austrailia

Let's find the portion of count of pixels for presumed vegetation fires vary across regions¶

we will develop a pie chart for this

In [16]:
plt.figure(figsize=(25, 15))
region_counts = df.groupby('Region')['Count'].sum()
plt.pie(region_counts, labels=region_counts.index, autopct='%5.1f%%')
plt.title('Percentage of Pixels for Presumed Vegetation Fires by Region')
plt.axis('equal')
plt.show()

Upon analysis, it is evident that the Northern Territory (NT) stands out prominently, showcasing the highest percentage of pixels associated with presumed vegetation fires. This finding suggests that NT experiences a significant proportion of these types of fires compared to other regions in the dataset

In [20]:
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='Mean_confidence', y='Mean_estimated_fire_radiative_power')
plt.xlabel('Mean Estimated Fire Radiative Power (MW)')
plt.ylabel('Mean Confidence')
plt.title('Mean Estimated Fire Radiative Power vs. Mean Confidence')
plt.show()

The scatter plot above illustrates the relationship between the mean estimated fire radiative power and the mean confidence level across the dataset. Each point on the plot represents an observation, with the x-axis denoting the mean estimated fire radiative power in megawatts (MW) and the y-axis representing the mean confidence level. It is worth noting that there are instances where the mean confidence level exceeds 2000

In [22]:
# instantiate a feature group 
aus_reg = folium.map.FeatureGroup()

# Create a Folium map centered on Australia
Aus_map = folium.Map(location=[-25, 135], zoom_start=4)

# loop through the region and add to feature group
for lat, lng, lab in zip(reg.Lat, reg.Lon, reg.region):
    aus_reg.add_child(
        folium.features.CircleMarker(
            [lat, lng],
            popup=lab,
            radius=5, # define how big you want the circle markers to be
            color='red',
            fill=True,
            fill_color='blue',
            fill_opacity=0.6
        )
    )

# add incidents to map
Aus_map.add_child(aus_reg)
